The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on Monday, described Sokoto State Governor, Aminu Tambuwal as a committed leader who works tirelessly towards the unity, stability, growth and electoral success of the party. The party made the commendation through its National Publicity Secretary, Hon. Debo Ologunagba, in a statement dated January 10, 2022. The statement further added that as the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Tambuwal, with excellent political dexterity, deepened our democratic practice for more transparent and productive governance. This, according to him, was done by reinforcing the principle of separation of power as well as asserting the independence of the legislature as enshrined in the 1999 Constitution (as amended). “As Governor, Rt. Hon. Aminu Waziri Tambuwal continues to display a remarkable commitment towards the wellbeing of his people as evident in his developmental projects in critical sectors including education, healthcare, agriculture, infrastructure and urban and rural development among others,” the statement said. He said Governor Tambuwal, who is also the Chairman of PDP Governors Forum, remains dedicated towards the success of the reconciliatory efforts in the party, adding that he has been pivotal in further repositioning the party as the platform for Nigerians to rescue and rebuild Nigeria from misrule. They PDP prayed to God to grant him many more years in good health for greater service to Nigeria and humanity at large.